<p class="hint-container-title">Problem Description</p>
<p>Given an integer <code v-pre>n</code>, place n queens on an <code v-pre>n Ã— n</code> chessboard such that no two queens attack each other. A queen can attack another queen if they are placed in <strong>the same row</strong>, <strong>the same column</strong>, or on <strong>the same diagonal</strong>.</p>
<p>Find <strong>all possible distinct arrangements</strong> of the queens on the board that satisfy these conditions.</p>
